    "subject": "Refactor and extend downloading code (cURL)",
    "description": "Code for downloading files using cURL is divided between client and common sources with very hacky bits of autoupdate code mixed in. It has to be moved in a single location and cleaned.\r\n\r\nThe following features should not be very hard to implement:\r\n\r\nh2. Multi-threaded downloads\r\n\r\nThere is a very simple example of how to use multithreaded downloads in cURL with pthread: http://curl.haxx.se/libcurl/c/multithread.html\r\n\r\nh2. Resume partial downloads\r\n\r\nAs user:TheDushan suggested, we should use @CURLOPT_RESUME_FROM@ if there is a .tmp file that we can resume from.\r\n\r\nExample of resumable download using cURL is on \"stackoverflow\":http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9409997/how-to-resume-file-download-through-ftp-using-curl-in-c\r\n",
